## Acceptance Criteria Results

| Criterion | Status |
|-----------|--------|
| `ReplayClock` provides virtual time that can run faster/slower than real time | **PASS** ΓÇö uses wall-clock anchoring with configurable speed multiplier; re-anchors on speed change |
| `set_speed(multiplier)` ΓÇö 1.0 = real-time, 10.0 = 10x, 0 = as-fast-as-possible | **PASS** ΓÇö `set_speed()` stores multiplier atomically; 0.0 triggers manual advance mode (no sleeping) |
| `now()` returns current virtual timestamp | **PASS** ΓÇö computes `virtual_origin + wall_elapsed * speed`, or returns `manual_now_` for speed=0 |
| `wait_until(timestamp)` blocks until virtual clock reaches timestamp | **PASS** ΓÇö sleeps via condition_variable with computed wall-time deadline; returns immediately for speed=0 or past timestamps |
| `ReplayEngine` reads tick data from TickStore, publishes events at correct virtual timestamps | **PASS** ΓÇö `load()` reads from TickStore and sorts by timestamp; `start()` iterates ticks, calling `wait_until` then invoking callback |
| Can feed directly into the pipeline (replacing MulticastReceiver) | **PASS** ΓÇö uses `ReplayCallback = std::function<void(const uint8_t*, size_t, uint64_t)>` matching `ReceiveCallback` signature |
| Build passes | **PASS** ΓÇö clean compilation, no warnings |

